#. Tag: title
#: glossary.docbook:2
#, no-c-format
msgid "Glossary"
msgstr "Glosar"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:4
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In this chapter you will find an explanation of most of the <quote>uncommon</"
"quote> words that are used in the handbook."
msgstr ""
"V tem poglavju boste našli razlago večine <quote>nepogostih</quote> besed, "
"ki se uporabljajo v priročniku."

#. Tag: glossterm
#: glossary.docbook:8
#, no-c-format
msgid "degrees"
msgstr "stopinj"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:9
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Degrees are units to measure angles or turns. A full turn is 360 degrees, a "
"half turn 180 degrees and a quarter turn 90 degrees. The commands "
"<userinput>turnleft</userinput>, <userinput>turnright</userinput> and "
"<userinput>direction</userinput> need an input in degrees."
msgstr ""
"Stopinje so enote za merjenje kotov ali obratov. Polni obrat je 360 stopinj, "
"polovični obrat 180 stopinj in četrtinski obrat 90 stopinj. Za ukaze "
"<userinput>turnleft</userinput>, <userinput>turnright</userinput> in "
"<userinput>direction</userinput> je treba vnesti stopinje."

#. Tag: glossterm
#: glossary.docbook:13
#, no-c-format
msgid "input and output of commands"
msgstr "ukazi za vhod in izhod"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:14
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Some commands take input, some commands give output, some commands take "
"input <emphasis>and</emphasis> give output and some commands neither take "
"input nor give output."
msgstr ""
"Nekateri ukazi sprejmejo vnos, nekateri ukazi dajo izhod, nekateri ukazi "
"sprejmejo vnos <emphasis>in</emphasis> dajo izhod in nekateri ukazi ne "
"sprejmejo niti vnosa niti ne dajo izhoda."

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:15
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Some examples of commands that only take input are: <screen>\n"
"forward 50\n"
"pencolor 255,0,0\n"
"print \"Hello!\"\n"
"</screen> The <userinput>forward</userinput> command takes <userinput>50</"
"userinput> as input. <userinput>forward</userinput> needs this input to know "
"how many <glossterm linkend=\"pixels\">pixels</glossterm> it should go "
"forward. <userinput>pencolor</userinput> takes a color as input and "
"<userinput>print</userinput> takes a string (a piece of text) as input. "
"Please note that the input can also be a container. The next example "
"illustrates this:"
msgstr ""
"Nekaj primerov ukazov, ki sprejemajo samo vnos, je: <screen>\n"
"naprej 50\n"
"pisalo 255,0,0\n"
"natisni \"Pozdravljeni!\"\n"
"</screen> Ukaz <userinput>forward</userinput> kot vhod sprejme "
"<userinput>50</userinput>. <userinput>forward</userinput> potrebuje ta vnos, "
"da ve, za koliko <glossterm linkend=\"pixels\">pikslov</glossterm> mora iti "
"naprej. <userinput>pencolor</userinput> sprejme barvo kot vhod, "
"<userinput>print</userinput> pa niz (del besedila) kot vhod. Upoštevajte, da "
"je vnos lahko tudi vsebnik. Naslednji primer to ponazarja:"

#. Tag: screen
#: glossary.docbook:18
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"$x = 50\n"
"print $x\n"
"forward 50\n"
"$str = \"hello!\"\n"
"print $str"
msgstr ""
"$x = 50\n"
"print $x\n"
"naprej 50\n"
"$str = \"zdravo!\"\n"
"print $str"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:20
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Now some examples of commands that give output: <screen>\n"
"$x = ask \"Please type something and press OK... thanks!\"\n"
"$r = random 1,100\n"
"</screen> The <userinput>ask</userinput> command takes a string as input, "
"and outputs the number or string that is entered. As you can see, the output "
"of <userinput>ask</userinput> is stored in the container <userinput>x</"
"userinput>. The <userinput>random</userinput> command also gives output. In "
"this case it outputs a number between 1 and 100. The output of the random is "
"again stored in a container, named <userinput>r</userinput>. Note that the "
"containers <userinput>x</userinput> and <userinput>r</userinput> are not "
"used in the example code above."
msgstr ""
"Zdaj nekaj primerov ukazov, ki dajejo izhod: <screen>\n"
"$x = ask \"Prosim, vnesite nekaj in pritisnite OK ... hvala!\"\n"
"$r = random 1.100\n"
"</screen> Ukaz <userinput>ask</userinput> vzame niz kot vhod in izpiše "
"vneseno število ali niz. Kot lahko vidite, je rezultat <userinput>ask</"
"userinput> shranjen v vsebniku <userinput>x</userinput>. Ukaz "
"<userinput>random</userinput> prav tako daje izhod. V tem primeru izpiše "
"število med 1 in 100. Izhod naključnega števila je ponovno shranjen v "
"vsebniku z imenom <userinput>r</userinput>. Upoštevajte, da vsebnika "
"<userinput>x</userinput> in <userinput>r</userinput> nista uporabljena v "
"zgornjem primeru kode."

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:24
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"There are also commands that neither need input nor give output. Here are "
"some examples:"
msgstr ""
"Obstajajo tudi ukazi, ki ne potrebujejo niti vnosa niti izhoda. Tukaj je "
"nekaj primerov:"

#. Tag: screen
#: glossary.docbook:25
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"clear\n"
"penup"
msgstr ""
"clear\n"
"penup"

#. Tag: glossterm
#: glossary.docbook:30
#, no-c-format
msgid "intuitive highlighting"
msgstr "intuitivno poudarjanje"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:31
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This is a feature of &kturtle; that makes coding even easier. With intuitive "
"highlighting the code that you write gets a color that indicates what type "
"of code it is. In the next list you will find the different types of code "
"and the color they get in <link linkend=\"the-editor\">the editor</link>."
msgstr ""
"To je zmožnost &kturtle; kar še olajša kodiranje. Z intuitivnim označevanjem "
"koda, ki jo napišete, dobi barvo, ki označuje, za katero vrsto kode gre. Na "
"naslednjem seznamu boste našli različne vrste kod in barve, ki jih dobijo v "
"<link linkend=\"the-editor\">urejevalniku</link>."

#. Tag: title
#: glossary.docbook:33
#, no-c-format
msgid "Different types of code and their highlight color"
msgstr "Različne vrste kode in njihova poudarjena barva"

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:37
#, no-c-format
msgid "regular commands"
msgstr "redni ukazi"

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:38
#, no-c-format
msgid "dark blue"
msgstr "temno modra"

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:39
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The regular commands are described <link linkend=\"commands\">here</link>."
msgstr "Običajni ukazi so opisani <link linkend=\"commands\">tukaj</link>."

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:42
#, no-c-format
msgid "execution controlling commands"
msgstr "ukazi za nadzor izvajanja"

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:43
#, no-c-format
msgid "black (bold)"
msgstr "črna (krepko)"

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:44
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"These special commands control execution, read more on them <link linkend="
"\"controlling-execution\">here</link>."
msgstr ""
"Ti posebni ukazi nadzorujejo izvajanje, preberite več o njih <link linkend="
"\"controlling-execution\">tukaj</link>."

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:47
#, no-c-format
msgid "comments"
msgstr "komentarji"

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:48 glossary.docbook:83
#, no-c-format
msgid "gray"
msgstr "siva"

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:49
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Lines that are commented start with a comment characters (#). These lines "
"are ignored when the code is executed. Comments allow the programmer to "
"explain a bit about his code or can be used to temporarily prevent a certain "
"piece of code from executing."
msgstr ""
"Vrstice, ki so komentirane, se začnejo z znaki za komentar (#). Te vrstice "
"se pri izvajanju kode ne upoštevajo. Komentarji programerju omogočajo, da "
"razloži nekaj o svoji kodi ali pa se lahko uporabijo za začasno preprečitev "
"izvajanja določenega dela kode."

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:52
#, no-c-format
msgid "brackets {, }"
msgstr "oklepaji {, }"

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:53
#, no-c-format
msgid "dark green (bold)"
msgstr "temno zelena (krepko)"

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:54
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Brackets are used to group portions of code. Brackets are often used "
"together with <link linkend=\"controlling-execution\">execution controllers</"
"link>."
msgstr ""
"Oklepaji se uporabljajo za združevanje delov kode. Oklepaji se pogosto "
"uporabljajo skupaj z <link linkend=\"controlling-execution\">krmilniki "
"izvajanja</link>."

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:57
#, no-c-format
msgid "the <link linkend=\"learn\">learn</link> command"
msgstr "ukaz <link linkend=\"learn\">nauči</link>"

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:58
#, no-c-format
msgid "light green (bold)"
msgstr "svetlo zelena (krepko)"

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:59
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <link linkend=\"learn\">learn</link> command is used to create new "
"commands."
msgstr ""
"Ukaz <link linkend=\"learn\">learn</link> se uporablja za ustvarjanje novih "
"ukazov."

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:62
#, no-c-format
msgid "strings"
msgstr "nizi"

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:63 glossary.docbook:125
#, no-c-format
msgid "<entry>red</entry>"
msgstr "<entry>rdeča</entry>"

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:64
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Not much to say about (text) strings either, except that they always start "
"and end with the double quotes (\")."
msgstr ""
"Tudi o (besedilnih) nizih ni kaj dosti povedati, le da se vedno začnejo in "
"končajo z dvojnimi narekovaji (\")."

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:67
#, no-c-format
msgid "numbers"
msgstr "števila"

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:68 glossary.docbook:73 glossary.docbook:126
#, no-c-format
msgid "dark red"
msgstr "temno rdeča"

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:69
#, no-c-format
msgid "Numbers, well not much to say about them."
msgstr "Števila, o njih ni kaj dosti za povedati."

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:72
#, no-c-format
msgid "boolean values"
msgstr "logične vrednosti"

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:74
#, no-c-format
msgid "There are exactly two boolean values, namely: true and false."
msgstr "Obstajata točno dve logični vrednosti, in sicer: true in false."

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:77
#, no-c-format
msgid "variables"
msgstr "spremenljivke"

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:78
#, no-c-format
msgid "purple"
msgstr "vijolična"

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:79
#, no-c-format
msgid "Start with a '$' and can contain numbers, strings or boolean values."
msgstr "Začne se z '$' in lahko vsebuje števila, nize ali logične vrednosti."

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:82
#, no-c-format
msgid "mathematical operators"
msgstr "matematični operatorji"

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:84
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"These are the mathematical operators: <userinput>+</userinput>, <userinput>-"
"</userinput>, <userinput>*</userinput>, <userinput>/</userinput> and "
"<userinput>^</userinput>."
msgstr ""
"To so matematični operatorji: <userinput>+</userinput>, <userinput>-</"
"userinput>, <userinput>*</userinput>, <userinput>/</userinput> in "
"<userinput>^</userinput> ."

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:87
#, no-c-format
msgid "comparison operators"
msgstr "primerjalni operaterji"

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:88
#, no-c-format
msgid "light blue (bold)"
msgstr "svetlo modra (krepko)"

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:89
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"These are the comparison operators: <userinput>==</userinput>, <userinput>!"
"=</userinput>, <userinput>&lt;</userinput>, <userinput>&gt;</userinput>, "
"<userinput>&lt;=</userinput> and <userinput>&gt;=</userinput>."
msgstr ""
"To so primerjalni operatorji: <userinput>==</userinput>, <userinput>!=</"
"userinput>, <userinput>&lt;</userinput>, <userinput>&gt;</userinput>, "
"<userinput>&lt;=</userinput> in <userinput>&gt;=</userinput>."

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:92
#, no-c-format
msgid "boolean operators"
msgstr "logični operatorji"

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:93
#, no-c-format
msgid "pink (bold)"
msgstr "roza (krepko)"

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:94
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"These are the boolean operators: <userinput>and</userinput>, <userinput>or</"
"userinput> and <userinput>not</userinput>."
msgstr ""
"To so logični operatorji: <userinput>in</userinput>, <userinput>ali</"
"userinput> in <userinput>ni</userinput>."

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:97
#, no-c-format
msgid "regular text"
msgstr "običajno besedilo"

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:98 glossary.docbook:123
#, no-c-format
msgid "black"
msgstr "črna"

#. Tag: glossterm
#: glossary.docbook:108
#, no-c-format
msgid "pixels"
msgstr "piksli"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:109
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A pixel is a dot on the screen. If you look very close you will see that the "
"screen of your monitor uses pixels. All images on the screen are built with "
"these pixels. A pixel is the smallest thing that can be drawn on the screen."
msgstr ""
"Piksel je pika na zaslonu. Če pogledate zelo natančno, boste videli, da "
"zaslon vašega monitorja uporablja slikovne pike. Vse slike na zaslonu so "
"zgrajene s temi slikovnimi pikami. Piksel je najmanjša stvar, ki jo lahko "
"narišemo na zaslonu."

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:110
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A lot of commands need a number of pixels as input. These commands are: "
"<userinput>forward</userinput>, <userinput>backward</userinput>, "
"<userinput>go</userinput>, <userinput>gox</userinput>, <userinput>goy</"
"userinput>, <userinput>canvassize</userinput> and <userinput>penwidth</"
"userinput>."
msgstr ""
"Številni ukazi potrebujejo število slikovnih pik kot vnos. Ti ukazi so: "
"<userinput>naprej</userinput>, <userinput>nazaj</userinput>, "
"<userinput>pojdi</userinput>, <userinput>pojdix</userinput>, "
"<userinput>pojdiy</userinput>, <userinput>velikost platna</userinput> in "
"<userinput>širina pisala</userinput>."

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:111
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In early versions of &kturtle; the canvas was essentially a raster image, "
"yet for recent versions the canvas is a vector drawing. This means that the "
"canvas can be zoomed in and out, therefore a pixel does not necessarily have "
"to translate to one dot on the screen."
msgstr ""
"V zgodnjih različicah &kturtle; platno je bilo v bistvu rastrska slika, "
"vendar je za novejše različice platno vektorska risba. To pomeni, da je "
"platno mogoče povečati in pomanjšati, zato ni nujno, da se piksel prevede v "
"eno točko na zaslonu."

#. Tag: glossterm
#: glossary.docbook:116
#, no-c-format
msgid "RGB combinations (color codes)"
msgstr "RGB kombinacije (barvne kode)"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:117
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"RGB combinations are used to describe colors. The <quote>R</quote> stand for "
"<quote>red</quote>, the <quote>G</quote> stands for <quote>green</quote> and "
"the <quote>B</quote> stands for <quote>blue</quote>. An example of an RGB "
"combination is <userinput>255,0,0</userinput>: the first value (<quote>red</"
"quote>) is 255 and the others are 0, so this represents a bright shade of "
"red. Each value of an RGB combination has to be in the range 0 to 255. Here "
"a small list of some often used colors:"
msgstr ""
"RGB kombinacije se uporabljajo za opisovanje barv. <quote>R</quote> pomeni "
"<quote>rdečo</quote>, <quote>G</quote> pomeni <quote>zeleno</quote> in "
"<quote>B</quote> pomeni za <quote>modro</quote>. Primer kombinacije RGB je "
"<userinput>255,0,0</userinput>: prva vrednost (<quote>rdeča</quote>) je 255, "
"druge pa 0, tako da to predstavlja svetel odtenek rdeče. Vsaka vrednost "
"kombinacije RGB mora biti v območju od 0 do 255. Tukaj je majhen seznam "
"nekaterih pogosto uporabljenih barv:"

#. Tag: title
#: glossary.docbook:119
#, no-c-format
msgid "Often used RGB combinations"
msgstr "Pogosto uporabljene kombinacije RGB"

#. Tag: userinput
#: glossary.docbook:123
#, no-c-format
msgid "0,0,0"
msgstr "0,0,0"

#. Tag: userinput
#: glossary.docbook:124
#, no-c-format
msgid "255,255,255"
msgstr "255,255,255"

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:124
#, no-c-format
msgid "white"
msgstr "bela"

#. Tag: userinput
#: glossary.docbook:125
#, no-c-format
msgid "255,0,0"
msgstr "255,0,0"

#. Tag: userinput
#: glossary.docbook:126
#, no-c-format
msgid "150,0,0"
msgstr "150,0,0"

#. Tag: userinput
#: glossary.docbook:127
#, no-c-format
msgid "0,255,0"
msgstr "0,255,0"

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:127
#, no-c-format
msgid "green"
msgstr "zelena"

#. Tag: userinput
#: glossary.docbook:128
#, no-c-format
msgid "0,0,255"
msgstr "0,0,255"

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:128
#, no-c-format
msgid "blue"
msgstr "modra"

#. Tag: userinput
#: glossary.docbook:129
#, no-c-format
msgid "0,255,255"
msgstr "0,255,255"

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:129
#, no-c-format
msgid "light blue"
msgstr "svetlo modra"

#. Tag: userinput
#: glossary.docbook:130
#, no-c-format
msgid "255,0,255"
msgstr "255,0,255"

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:130
#, no-c-format
msgid "pink"
msgstr "roza"

#. Tag: userinput
#: glossary.docbook:131
#, no-c-format
msgid "255,255,0"
msgstr "255,255,0"

#. Tag: entry
#: glossary.docbook:131
#, no-c-format
msgid "yellow"
msgstr "rumena"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:136
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Two commands need an RGB combination as input: these commands are "
"<userinput>canvascolor</userinput> and <userinput>pencolor</userinput>."
msgstr ""
"Dva ukaza potrebujeta kombinacijo RGB kot vhod: ta ukaza sta "
"<userinput>barva platna</userinput> in <userinput>barva pisala</userinput>."

#. Tag: glossterm
#: glossary.docbook:140
#, no-c-format
msgid "sprite"
msgstr "sprite"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:141
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A sprite is a small picture that can be moved around the screen. Our beloved "
"turtle, for instance, is a sprite."
msgstr ""
"Sprite je majhna slika, ki jo je mogoče premikati po zaslonu. Naša ljubljena "
"želva je na primer sprite."

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:142
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"With this version of &kturtle; the sprite cannot be changed from a turtle "
"into something else. Future versions of &kturtle; will be able to do this."
msgstr ""
"S to različico &kturtle; sprite ni mogoče spremeniti iz želve v nekaj "
"drugega. Prihodnje različice &kturtle; bodo to zmogle."
